g.text: Access control lists - who can create/delete queues or publish/subscribe
Max number of queues allowed in the repository
Default queue settings (applied to new queues)
Auto-creation of queues when messages arrive for non-existent topics
Repository-wide default message TTL (time to live)
Storage limits (max size for all queues combined)
Maximum queue size (number of messages or byte size)
Rate limiting for producers (messages per second)
Idle timeout (how long before disconnecting an inactive consumer)
Topic filter patterns (regex or wildcard-based subscriptions)
Maximum in-flight messages (how many unacknowledged messages allowed)
Acknowledgment timeout (how long before message is redelivered)
Message prefetch count (number of messages to buffer client-side)
Consumer priority (for prioritized message delivery in shared mode)
Rate limiting (messages per second the consumer can receive)
Delivery delay (minimum time between message deliveries)
Dead letter policy (where to send messages that fail processing)
Notification thresholds (e.g., alert if consumer falls behind)
